irth%20of%20my%20second%20son%20wasn't%20easy.%20But%20one%20thing%20made%20all%20the%20difference%20in%20this%20transition.%20My%20husband%20decided%20to%20resign%20from%20his%20job%20so%20he%20could%20bond%20with%20our%20youngest%20while%20also%20supporting%20our%20oldest%20in%20starting%20school.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20original%20plan%20was%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoing-back-to-work-after-baby-maternity-leave-judgment-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereturn%20to%20work%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20after%20six%20months%2C%20as%20I'm%20self-employed%20as%20a%20freelance%20journalist.%20I%20was%20largely%20offline%20for%20the%20first%20three%20months%20after%20giving%20birth%3B%20I%20wanted%20to%20give%20myself%20permission%20to%20just%20exist%20in%20that%20new%20baby%20bubble.%20But%20I%20was%20conscious%20that%20the%20more%20time%20I%20spent%20away%20from%20work%2C%20the%20more%20it%20was%20costing%20me%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20financially%2C%20but%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20momentum%20I'd%20built%20in%20my%20career.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20financial%20freedom%20to%20have%20just%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmothers-childcare-working-parents-moms-good-bad-news-why-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eone%20parent%20working%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20an%20entire%20year%20is%20not%20something%20I%20have%20taken%20lightly.%20Yet%20the%20most%20memorable%20and%20impactful%20parts%20of%20my%20year%20with%20a%20stay-at-home%20husband%20are%20not%20the%20amazing%20home-cooked%20meals%20he%20made%20(and%20continues%20to)%20but%20how%20it's%20helped%20us%20see%20what%20true%20partnership%20is%20and%20define%20how%20we%20want%20to%20live%20our%20lives%2C%20the%20role%20we%20want%20work%20to%20play%2C%20and%20the%20kind%20of%20parents%20we%20want%20to%20be.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226e218bc4-b665-4c6a-b303-d17f3f514a4d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe've%20worked%20to%20challenge%20stereotypes%20in%20our%20relationship%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20took%20a%20yearlong%20maternity%20leave%20when%20I%20had%20my%20first%20son%2C%20and%20though%20we%20technically%20fit%20into%20the%20outdated%20stereotypes%20of%20%26quot%3Bbreadwinner%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhomemaker%26quot%3B%20during%20that%20time%2C%20I%20often%20felt%20isolated%20without%20the%20connection%20of%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EThat's%20why%2C%20when%20my%20husband%20made%20the%20choice%20to%20be%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-provider-stay-at-home-dad-husband-kids-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estay-at-home%20dad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20just%20be%20unavailable%20all%20day%2C%20buried%20in%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20knew%20all%20too%20well%20the%20feelings%20of%20resentment%2C%20loneliness%2C%20and%20frustration%20that%20can%20crop%20up%20when%20you're%20with%20the%20kids%20on%20your%20own%2C%20envious%20of%20your%20partner's%20ability%20to%20have%20conversations%20with%20co-workers%2C%20uninterrupted%20lunches%2C%20and%20hot%20coffee.%20So%20I%20tried%20to%20be%20the%20working%20partner%20I%20would%20want%20if%20I%20were%20a%20stay-at-home%20parent%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20who%20could%20sense%20when%20another%20pair%20of%20hands%20could%20help%20take%20the%20edge%20off%20a%20messy%20lunch%20or%20out-of-control%20tantrum.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20had%20a%20fluid%20setup.%20In%20between%20working%2C%20I%20changed%20nappies%2C%20helped%20make%20snacks%20and%20lunches%2C%20washed%20dishes%2C%20and%20hung%20up%20laundry%20(I%20was%20also%20breastfeeding%20our%20youngest).%20Our%20house%20and%20family%20are%20a%20shared%20effort%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20person%20who%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-moms-deserve-government-aid-for-unpaid-labor-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edoesn't%20do%20paid%20work%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It's%20a%20mindset%20I%20think%20more%20working%20dads%20could%20adopt%20to%20ease%20the%20%26quot%3Bmotherload%26quot%3B%20that%20many%20moms%20struggle%20with%2C%20including%20those%20who%20are%20working.%20Individually%2C%20we're%20not%20simply%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-jealous-made-more-money-breadwinner-relationship-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebreadwinner%20or%20homemaker%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We're%20a%20partnership.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MaryLou%20Costa%20and%20her%20child%20in%20a%20pool%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6669a25eed9a404d829cc1e7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaryLou%20Costa%20pitched%20in%20while%20her%20husband%20was%20a%20stay-at-home%20dad.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20MaryLou%20Costa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22400b0558-5004-40d1-b31e-683f182226fd%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20double%20standards%20while%20my%20husband%20was%20a%20stay-at-home%20dad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20my%20husband%20was%20a%20stay-at-home%20dad%2C%20it%20opened%20my%20eyes%20to%20double%20standards.%20I%20was%20often%20told%20I%20was%20lucky%20to%20have%20him%2C%20but%20no%20one%20ever%20noticed%20that%20as%20a%20stay-at-home%20parent%2C%20he%20was%20also%20lucky%20to%20have%20such%20an%20involved%2C%20hands-on%20working%20partner.%20It's%20something%20dads%20are%20often%20congratulated%20for%2C%20yet%20it's%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-unread-emails-give-up-inbox-zero-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexpected%20of%20working%20moms%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I%20was%20also%20regularly%20asked%20when%20he%20would%20be%20going%20back%20to%20work%2C%20as%20if%20it%20was%20assumed%20he%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20be%20a%20stay-at-home%20dad%20permanently.%20When%20I%20had%20my%20year%20at%20home%2C%20I%20was%20often%20asked%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eif%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20was%20going%20back%20to%20work%2C%20rather%20than%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhen%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20husband%20recently%20started%20working%20full-time%20again%20%E2%80%94%20a%20decision%20made%20for%20financial%20reasons%20but%20also%20because%20he%20needs%20to%20keep%20his%20career%20moving%20again.%20The%20new%20norms%20we've%20tried%20to%20create%20have%20since%20been%20difficult%20to%20uphold.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20is%20in%20the%20office%20just%20two%20days%20a%20week%2C%20so%20we%20still%20share%20domestic%20tasks%20fairly%20evenly.%20Being%20self-employed%2C%20though%2C%20I%20work%20most%20flexibly%2C%20meaning%20I%2C%20like%20most%20moms%2C%20have%20become%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdefault-parent-hard-spend-time-kids-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edefault%20parent%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20medical%20or%20dental%20appointments%20or%20appearances%20at%20school%20for%20performances%20or%20sports%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MaryLou%20Costa's%20husband%20with%20their%20two%20kids%20by%20the%20ocean.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6669a282764df1611258d454%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaryLou%20Costa's%20husband%20has%20returned%20to%20work%20full-time.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20MaryLou%20Costa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20just%20easier%20for%20it%20to%20be%20me%20rather%20than%20have%20my%20husband%20create%20tension%20among%20his%20new%20colleagues%20and%20get%20a%20reputation%20for%20being%20unreliable%20while%20he's%20still%20new.%20That%20conflict%20is%20something%20working%20moms%20are%20expected%20to%20accept%20while%20working%20dads'%20lives%20at%20home%20are%20often%20overlooked%3B%20the%20stereotypes%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bbreadwinner%20dad%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhomemaker%20mom%26quot%3B%20are%20still%20very%20much%20alive%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20and%20it%20can%20feel%20intimidating%20to%20openly%20challenge%20those.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20an%20ideal%20world%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20would%20both%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffour-day-workweek-backed-by-most-young-people-survey-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ework%20four%20days%20a%20week%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20get%20some%20of%20that%20equality%20back%20that%20we've%20been%20striving%20for.%20Financially%2C%20we%20could%20make%20this%20work%2C%20but%20he%20doesn't%20yet%20feel%20comfortable%20making%20that%20request.%20For%20now%2C%20I%20have%20cut%20work%20down%20from%20nearly%20full-time%20to%20just%20over%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20as%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20miss%20time%20with%20our%20youngest%20by%20sending%20him%20to%20day%20care%20full-time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGoing%20to%20things%20like%20toddler%20yoga%20with%20him%20and%20swimming%20lessons%20with%20my%20oldest%20gives%20me%20great%20bonding%20moments%20with%20my%20kids%2C%20which%20I'll%20never%20regret.%20There%20are%20two%20things%20I%20can't%20deny%2C%20though%20%E2%80%94%20I%20get%20a%20lot%20out%20of%20working%2C%20and%20falling%20into%20that%20breadwinner%2Fhomemaker%20dynamic%20again%20feels%20like%20a%20step%20backward.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20I%20understand%20that%20pushing%20boundaries%20takes%20not%20just%20confidence%20but%20time%20and%20space%2C%20too.%20Just%20as%20my%20husband%20gave%20me%20the%20time%20and%20space%20to%20give%20my%20career%20the%20extra%20push%20it%20needed%20after%20having%20our%20second%20son%2C%20I%20am%20now%20here%20to%20do%20the%20same%20for%20him.%20And%20I'd%20argue%20that's%20just%20as%20important%20in%20terms%20of%20true%20equality.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstay-at-home-dad-breadwinner-mom-double-standards-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718446081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6669a366764df1611258d4e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstay-at-home-dad-breadwinner-mom-double-standards-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20husband%20was%20a%20stay-at-home%20dad%20for%20a%20year%20while%20I%20was%20the%20breadwinner.%20Here%20are%20the%20lessons%20we%20learned%2C%20and%20how%20our%20relationship%20has%20changed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(MaryLou%20Costa)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstay-at-home-dad-breadwinner-mom-double-standards-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22America's%20way%20of%20measuring%20poverty%20is%20stuck%20in%20the%201960s.%20Here's%20how%20we%20can%20fix%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hands%20breaking%20a%20line%20graph%20representing%20a%20poverty%20trend%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c936ded9a404d829e0b4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20argue%20the%20poverty