-constrained%2C%20and%20employed.%20Many%20forms%20of%20help%20are%20tied%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-class-americans-earning-above-poverty-struggles-afford-food-medicine-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20poverty%20line%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20calculated%20using%20a%20formula%20that%20has%20largely%20not%20been%20updated%20since%20the%201960s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jason%20Hopkins%20and%20cat%20Nyx%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F666c7f6d764df161125a0ea7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJason%20Hopkins%20and%20cat%20Nyx.%3Cp%3EJason%20Hopkins%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20way%20we%20measure%20poverty%20is%20incredibly%20outdated%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Beth%20Jarosz%2C%20senior%20program%20director%20at%20the%20Population%20Reference%20Bureau%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20organization%20that%20conducts%20demographic%20analyses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20has%20heard%20stories%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-lower-income-alice-paycheck-to-paycheck-minimum-wage-insecurity-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparents%20forced%20to%20choose%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20putting%20food%20on%20the%20table%20and%20supporting%20their%20children's%20education%2C%20older%20adults%20worried%20they%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-peak-boomer-alice-social-security-masters-degree-student-loans-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enever%20be%20able%20to%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdinks-childfree-parents-choice-kids-childless-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildfree%20couples%3C%2Fa%3E%20unable%20to%20access%20social%20services%2C%20and%20individuals%20concerned%20they%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20down%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20households%20could%20use%20more%20access%20to%20social%20assistance%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20US'%20poverty%20threshold%20is%20leaving%20them%20behind.%20If%20America%20modernized%20its%20way%20of%20measuring%20economic%20needs%2C%20millions%20of%20low-income%20families%20could%20better%20make%20ends%20meet.%20The%20real%20question%20is%20whether%20the%20US%20ever%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2241f17220-a392-4d67-ac85-197cf1416d93%5C%22%3EThe%20poverty%20line%20is%20calculated%20in%20an%20outdated%20way%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthcare.gov%2Fglossary%2Ffederal-poverty-level-fpl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20poverty%20line%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%2048%20contiguous%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20is%20%2415%2C060%20a%20year%20for%20one%20person%2C%20%2420%2C440%20for%20a%20family%20of%20two%2C%20and%20%2431%2C200%20for%20a%20family%20of%20four.%20This%20does%20not%20vary%20by%20location%20or%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20but%20it's%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStraight%20up%2C%20it%20is%20too%20low.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20sufficient%20way%20to%20measure%20how%20current%20families%20are%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Kyle%20Ross%2C%20a%20policy%20analyst%20for%20inclusive%20economy%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20American%20Progress%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20most%20recent%20Census%20data%2C%20the%20official%20poverty%20rate%20in%202022%20was%2011.5%25%2C%20or%20about%2037.9%20million%20Americans.%20In%202022%2C%2042%25%20of%20Americans%20were%20below%20the%20ALICE%20threshold%2C%20the%20amount%20households%20need%20to%20cover%20their%20essential%20costs%2C%20according%20to%20research%20organization%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unitedforalice.org%2Fnational-overview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnited%20For%20ALICE%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMollie%20Orshansky%2C%20a%20government%20worker%2C%20originally%20estimated%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line%20formula%20in%20the%201960s%20using%20USDA%20data%2C%20which%20showed%20people%20often%20spent%20around%20a%20third%20of%20their%20income%20on%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20account%20for%20how%20Americans%20actually%20live.%20Americans%20now%20spend%20just%20around%2013%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20groceries%2C%20as%20food%20prices%20have%20fallen%20relative%20to%20incomes%20and%20housing%20costs%20have%20risen%20disproportionately.%20According%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20people%20spent%2033.3%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20housing%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20way%20that%20costs%20have%20changed%2C%20the%20poverty%20measure%20that's%20just%20based%20on%20how%20much%20you're%20spending%20on%20groceries%20really%20does%20not%20reflect%20what%20people%20are%20paying%20for%20their%20expenses%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Jarosz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%2030%20government%20programs%20use%20the%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%20poverty%20guidelines%20%E2%80%94%20or%20higher%20percentages%20based%20on%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line%20%E2%80%94%20to%20determine%20eligibility%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Assistance%20Program%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-assistance-food-stamps-snap-doesnt-help-low-income-dinks-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESNAP%3C%2Fa%3E)%20is%20capped%20at%20130%25%20of%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fns.usda.gov%2Fsnap%2Frecipient%2Feligibility%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242%2C694%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20gross%20monthly%20income%20for%20a%20family%20of%20three%20%E2%80%94%20while%20the%20Special%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Program%20for%20Women%2C%20Infants%2C%20and%20Children%20(WIC)%20is%20185%25%20%E2%80%94%20%2447%2C767%20a%20year%20for%20a%20family%20of%20three.%20Head%20Start%2C%20the%20National%20School%20Lunch%20Program%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20Medicare%20and%20Medicaid%20are%20among%20other%20programs%20relying%20on%20federal%20poverty%20line%20eligibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20some%20outlier%20programs%20like%20Supplemental%20Security%20Income%2C%20the%20Earned%20Income%20Tax%20Credit%2C%20and%20Section%208%20low-income%20housing%20assistance%20do%20not%20rely%20on%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20much%20of%20federal%20policy%2C%20state%20policy%20is%20focused%20around%20the%20poverty%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20Stephanie%20Hoopes%2C%20national%20director%20at%20United%20For%20ALICE%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20all%20leading%20to%20an%20ever-widening%20gap%20of%20Americans%20who%20are%20technically%20in%20poverty%20but%20still%20aren't%20getting%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FI6HWo%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22ALICE%20household%20rate%20vs.%20poverty%20household%20rate%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22444%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20thresholds%20have%20a%20cliff%20problem%20where%20they%20often%20become%20a%20trap%20where%20you%20have%20someone%20who%20is%20at%20a%20very%20low-income%20level%20and%20work%20because%20oftentimes%20programs%20have%20work%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20Jarosz%20said.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20over%20the%20holidays%2C%20they%20get%20an%20additional%20shift%20that%20they've%20picked%20up%2C%20and%20that%20bumps%20their%20income%20up%20just%20enough%20that%20they%20lose%20their%20Medicaid%20coverage%20that%20month.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20financial%20cliff%20has%20left%20people%20like%20Melinda%20Binkley%2C%2056%2C%20%26quot%3Bless%20than%20%24100%26quot%3B%20away%20from%20receiving%20SNAP%20or%20rental%20assistance%20but%20struggling%20to%20keep%20a%20roof%20over%20her%20family's%20head%20in%20Stillwater%2C%20Minnesota.%20Ryan%20Arbuckle%2C%2036%2C%20also%20doesn't%20qualify%20for%20government%20help%20on%20his%20IT%20job%20salary.%20He's%20a%20single%20father%20to%20five%20children%20near%20St.%20Louis%20and%20can%20barely%20afford%20groceries%20and%20utility%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOleg%20Parubin%2C%20a%2045-year-old%20security%20guard%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20makes%20%2445%2C000%20a%20year%20but%20struggles%20to%20afford%20insulin%20for%20his%20Type%201%20diabetes%20and%20worries%20about%20eviction.%20Once%20he%20started%20making%20more%20at%20his%20job%2C%20he%20became%20ineligible%20for%20various%20benefits%20such%20as%20SNAP%20or%20reduced-fare%20transportation%2C%20which%20he%20estimates%20amounted%20to%20over%20%2410%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20lost%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20able%20to%20find%20an%20answer%20to%20how%20people%20can%20make%20it%20today%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Parubin%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20decided%20it%20is%20a%20faulty%20system%2C%20something%20is%20broken%20and%20doesn't%20work%20properly.%20But%20I%20still%20don't%20know%20what%20can%20I%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20survive%2C%20these%20Americans%20who%20fall%20outside%20financial%20safety%20nets%20have%20resorted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-healthcare-plasma-gen-x-government-assistance-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eselling%20plasma%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20extra%20income%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnap-alice-food-stamps-hunger-government-assitance-free-meals-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskipping%20meals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20risking%20the%20loss%20of%20their%20electricity%20or%20water%20supply%20because%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-class-ame