0rental%20voucher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20homeless%20enough%20to%20get%20certain%20help%20because%20I%20have%20a%20roof%20over%20my%20head%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-poor-enough-low-income-millennial-cant-afford-rent-homeless-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshe%20previously%20told%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I'm%20too%20homeless%20to%20get%20a%20job%20because%20I%20don't%20know%20where%20I'm%20going%20to%20live%20in%20three%20weeks.%20What%20do%20you%20do%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22834%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Melissa%20in%20a%20cap%20and%20gown%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66422023f27898f532d6e665%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221114%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMelissa%20Hedden's%20household%20income%20is%20above%20the%20poverty%20line%2C%20but%20she%20struggles%20to%20afford%20housing%20and%20healthcare.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Melissa%20Hedden%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20resistance%20to%20changing%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line%20could%20stem%20from%20the%20government's%20desire%20not%20to%20inflate%20the%20number%20of%20people%20in%20poverty%20overnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20really%20wants%20to%20be%20the%20politician%20that%20is%20behind%20an%20increase%20in%20poverty%2C%26quot%3B%20Ross%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20it%20may%20be%20a%20more%20accurate%20representation%20of%20how%20Americans%20are%20really%20doing%20financially%2C%20it%20looks%20pretty%20concerning%20on%20paper.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpanding%20eligibility%20would%20also%20mean%20that%2C%20intuitively%2C%20more%20people%20would%20receive%20assistance%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20could%20cost%20a%20lot%20more%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can%20definitely%20be%20a%20costly%20measure%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Ross%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20personally%20think%20that%20would%20be%20worth%20it%3B%20already%2C%20these%20programs%20are%20not%20meeting%20the%20needs%20of%20families%20as%20they%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20barriers%20to%20updating%20the%20poverty%20line%20are%20political.%20Congress%20would%20need%20to%20pass%20legislation%20in%20order%20to%20officially%20change%20the%20way%20the%20US%20measures%20economic%20need%2C%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwaysandmeans.house.gov%2F2023%2F10%2F25%2Ffive-key-moments-from-work-welfare-subcommittee-hearing-on-measuring-poverty%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiden%20administration%20would%20have%20to%20step%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20would%20both%20be%20unlikely%20in%20such%20a%20polarized%20political%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBills%20that%20expand%20social%20services%20and%20tax%20credits%20are%20also%20expensive%20and%20historically%20difficult%20to%20pass%20%E2%80%94%20most%20recently%2C%20with%20the%20expanded%20child%20tax%20credit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F19thnews.org%2F2024%2F04%2Fchild-tax-credit-tax-day-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20stalled%20in%20the%20Senate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20plans%20to%20expand%20Medicaid%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fhealth-shots%2F2024%2F05%2F16%2F1251691921%2Fmedicaid-expansion-mississippi-alabama-south%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblocked%20in%20multiple%20states%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5b4fdda-9f46-4a64-81a7-1f13a92afe7b%5C%22%3EExperts%20differ%20on%20how%20to%20fix%20poverty%20measures%2C%20but%20there%20is%20already%20progress%20on%20solutions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20researchers%20differ%20on%20how%20the%20poverty%20line%20should%20be%20tweaked%2C%20many%20agree%20it%20needs%20an%20overhaul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20the%20poverty%20level%20is%20too%20low%20to%20reflect%20the%20true%20number%20of%20people%20who%20are%20in%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20Jarosz%20said.%20%26quot%3BIs%20there%20really%20a%20need%20to%20have%20a%20threshold%3F%20Is%20there%20really%20a%20need%20to%20have%20a%20cap%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Ross%20said%20that%20even%20if%20thresholds%20don't%20change%2C%20programs%20could%20still%20work%20to%20eliminate%20many%20barriers%20to%20entry%2C%20like%20burdensome%20application%20processes%20%E2%80%94%20making%20them%20more%20accessible%20to%20people%20who%20do%20qualify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Kevin%20Mullin%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20California%2C%20has%20introduced%20legislation%20%E2%80%94%20called%20the%20Poverty%20Line%20Act%E2%80%94%20that%20would%20modernize%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20actual%20costs%20of%20goods%20and%20how%20prices%20differ%20across%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20current%20poverty%20line%20is%20woefully%20out%20of%20touch%20with%20the%20realities%20that%20Americans%20face%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Mullin%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20line%20doesn't%20account%20for%20how%20costs%20vary%20across%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20for%20key%20essentials%20like%20childcare%20and%20home%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20many%20working%20families%20make%20too%20little%20to%20afford%20their%20basic%20needs%2C%20yet%20because%20the%20federal%20poverty%20line%20is%20so%20low%2C%20they%20are%20not%20eligible%20for%20safety%20net%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20Mullin%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20poverty%20line%20probably%20won't%20be%20changed%20for%20some%20time%2C%20Jarosz%20said%2C%20given%20how%20many%20benefits%20programs%20rely%20on%20it.%20Still%2C%20there%20is%20precedent%20for%20programs%20providing%20more%20widespread%20boosts%20or%20sidestepping%20stringent%20eligibility%20and%20spending%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20universal%20or%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20model%2C%20which%20typically%20gives%20participants%20between%20%24100%20and%20%241%2C0