%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERunning%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20mainstay%20in%20the%20fitness%20world%2C%20only%20continues%20to%20grow%20in%20popularity.%20Last%20year's%20New%20York%20City%20Marathon%20was%20the%20largest%20ever%2C%20with%2051%2C933%20runners%2C%20an%20increase%20of%20about%204%2C000%20from%202022.%20And%20165%2C000%20people%20have%20applied%20for%20the%202024%20race%2C%20the%20second%20most%20ever%2C%20behind%20only%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabc7ny.com%2Fnew-york-city-marathon-runners-drawing-nyrr%2F14584663%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520New%2520York%2520Road%2520Runners%2Cmost%2520ever%252C%2520behind%2520only%25202020.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EABC%207%20NY%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%20rucking%2C%20which%20involves%20walking%20or%20jogging%20with%20a%20weighted%20backpack%2C%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20buzziest%20trends%20in%20fitness.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguy-fieri-weight-loss-healthy-aging-fat-burning-rucking-workouts-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGuy%20Fieri%20said%20he%20lost%2030%20pounds%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20by%20hiking%20with%20a%20weighted%20vest%20uphill%20a%20few%20times%20a%20week%20(alongside%20eating%20a%20healthy%20diet)%2C%20and%20it's%20beloved%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frucking-startup-founders-investors-look-for-ways-optimize-workouts-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESilicon%20Valley%3C%2Fa%3E%20elites%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frucking-benefits-tia-clair-toomey-orr-crossfit-games-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegendary%20CrossFitters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ead3e7f3-6d18-4269-acf4-5d507e28edf5%5C%22%3ERucking%20and%20running%20are%20both%20great%20aerobic%20exercises%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAerobic%20exercise%2C%20which%20both%20activities%20count%20as%2C%20can%20increase%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvo2-max-explained-what-is-good-how-improve-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecardiovascular%20fitness%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20endurance%2C%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20cardiovascular%20disease%2C%20and%20improve%20risk%20factors%20such%20as%20blood%20pressure%2C%20cholesterol%2C%20and%20insulin%20sensitivity%2C%20Dr.%20Allison%20Zielinski%2C%20a%20cardiologist%20and%20co-director%20of%20the%20sports%20cardiology%20program%20at%20Northwestern%20Memorial%20Hospital%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigher%20levels%20of%20fitness%20are%20also%20linked%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fessential-healthy-habits-for-your-twenties-thirties-longevity-advice-2023-12%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elonger%20lifespan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20said%3A%20Cardio%20lowers%20the%20risk%20of%20early%20death%20from%20any%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuke%20Worthington%2C%20a%20top%20trainer%20and%20sports%20scientist%20whose%20clients%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrity-trainer-luke-worthington-workout-dakota-johnson-naomi-campbell-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENaomi%20Campbell%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Dakota%20Fanning%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20walking%20and%20running%20can%20improve%20body%20composition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20some%20%26quot%3Bhidden%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Rotating%20your%20pelvis%20and%20ribcage%2C%20which%20you%20automatically%20do%20when%20you%20walk%20or%20run%2C%20can%20help%20the%20digestive%20system%20run%20more%20smoothly%20and%20improve%20the%20movement%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Flymphatic-drainage-massage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elymphatic%20fluids%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20outdoors%20can%20also%20boost%20your%20mood%20and%20calm%20the%20nervous%20system.%20The%20adjustment%20and%20re-adjustment%20that%20the%20eyes%20and%20brain%20continually%20make%20when%20walking%20or%20running%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20improve%20parasympathetic%20nervous%20system%20activity%2C%20Worthington%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20man%20and%20a%20women%20wearing%20backpacks%20and%20walking%20on%20a%20gravel%20path%20through%20the%20woods%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654eab65b788914e55547109%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20way%20of%20rucking%20is%20walking%20with%20a%20weighted%20backpack.%20%3Cp%3Eurbazon%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2261a61366-9919-4168-8fba-14045def94de%5C%22%3ECarrying%20weight%20is%20good%20for%20bone%20health%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20difference%20between%20rucking%20and%20running%20is%20the%20weight-carrying%20component.%20Walking%20with%20an%20additional%20load%20requires%20more%20work%20from%20the%20cardiovascular%20system%20and%20some%20of%20your%20muscles%20than%20unloaded%20walking%2C%20Zielinski%20said.%20So%20it%20uses%20up%20more%20energy%20and%20burns%20more%20calories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20health%20benefit%20or%20quantity%20of%20fat%20you%20lose%20from%20rucking%20and%20running%20will%20depend%20on%20factors%20like%20speed%2C%20terrain%2C%20hill%20grade%2C%20duration%2C%20and%20how%20much%20load%20you%20carry%2C%20she%20said.%20You're%20going%20to%20get%20more%20of%20a%20workout%20from%20sprinting%20up%20a%20hill%20than%20you%20would%20from%20strolling%20with%20five%20pounds%20on%20your%20back%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20carrying%20a%20load%2C%20which%20humans%20have%20done%20for%20centuries%2C%20can%20be%20beneficial%20for%20bone%20health%2C%20Worthington%20said.%20Applying%20force%20along%20the%20length%20of%20long%20bones%2C%20known%20as%20axial%20loading%20of%20the%20skeleton%2C%20is%20really%20great%20for%20maintaining%20bone%20and%20mass%20density%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20because%20adding%20weight%20feels%20more%20difficult%2C%20it%20can%20create%20a%20higher%20sense%20of%20achievement%2C%20Worthington%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a486695d-a055-4eef-a2c8-e0eb23647a97%5C%22%3ECardio%20won't%20help%20you%20build%20muscle%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorthington%20said%20that%20neither%20exercise%20would%20have%20any%20noticeable%20impact%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-exercises-build-upper-body-muscle-short-time-gym-workout-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20muscle%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20weight%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweight-lifting-rep-range-rule-myth-how-train-build-muscle-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIncreasing%20muscle%20mass%3C%2Fa%3E%20requires%20three%20things%3A%20A%20calorie%20surplus%20(because%20you%20can't%20make%20something%20out%20of%20nothing)%2C%20adequate%20protein%2C%20(the%20building%20blocks%20of%20muscle%20tissue)%2C%20and%20gradually%20increasing%20workload%20over%20time%2C%20(whether%20through%20increased%20weight%20or%20mechanical%20tension)%2C%20Worthington%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221a28caac-16b5-4adc-9d82-5e6f8a7ce858%5C%22%3EChoose%20whatever%20you're%20likely%20to%20do%20regularly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20looking%20to%20establish%20an%20exercise%20regime%2C%20start%20slow%20and%20aim%20to%20be%20consistent%2C%20the%20experts%20recommended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20that%20for%20people%20who%20are%20not%20exercising%2C%20starting%20with%20walking%2C%20adding%20some%20grade%2C%20and%20then%20once%20they%20kind%20of%20get%20comfortable%20with%20that%20and%20feel%20like%20that's%20not%20very%20hard%20anymore%2C%20then%20adding%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20weight%20can%20up%20the%20intensity%2C%26quot%3B%20Zielinski%20said.%20This%20migh