e%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20caveats%20are%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFirst%2C%20two%20individuals%20who%20became%20Prime%20Minister%20after%20the%20elections%20contested%20from%20two%20seats.%20They%20won%20both%20seats%20and%20the%20seat%20they%20retained%20is%20considered.%20Indira%20Gandhi%20won%20from%20Raebareli%20and%20Medak%20in%201980%20and%20retained%20the%20latter.%20Narendra%20Modi%20won%20from%20Vadodara%20and%20Varanasi%20in%202014%20and%20retained%20Varanasi.%20One%20sitting%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Narasimha%20Rao%2C%20contested%20from%20two%20seats%20in%201996%2C%20Nandyal%20and%20Berhampur.%20He%20won%20both%20and%20retained%20Berhampur%2C%20so%20that%20seat%20is%20considered.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESecond%2C%20in%20the%20elections%20of%201952%20and%201957%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20won%20from%20a%20double-member%20constituency%2C%20where%20voters%20had%20two%20votes.%20This%20factor%20is%20considered%20while%20calculating%20the%20percentage%20of%20votes%20he%20secured.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2015%20instances%20of%20sitting%20Prime%20Ministers%20contesting%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20In%2011%20cases%2C%20sitting%20Prime%20Ministers%20returned%20to%20the%20position%20after%20the%20election.%20In%20six%20cases%2C%20sitting%20Prime%20Ministers%20left%20office%20as%20their%20party%2Falliance%20was%20unable%20to%20secure%20a%20majority.%20Notably%2C%20in%20three%20of%20the%2021%20examples%20where%20the%20candidates%20secured%20less%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20votes%2C%20they%20were%20sitting%20Prime%20Ministers.%20One%20returned%20to%20power%2C%20while%20two%20had%20to%20relinquish%20office%20as%20their%20party%2Falliance%20lost%20a%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20PMs%20Won%20Majority%20Of%20Votes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%2018%20cases%20where%20the%20sitting%20Prime%20Minister%20or%20prospective%20Prime%20Minister%20won%20by%20a%20majority%20of%20votes%20in%20their%20constituency.%20Twelve%20of%20them%20were%20sitting%20Prime%20Ministers%3A%20eight%20returned%20to%20power%20after%20the%20election%2C%20while%20four%20resigned%20as%20Prime%20Minister%20as%20their%20party%2Falliance%20lost.%20In%20the%20remaining%20six%20cases%2C%20they%20became%20Prime%20Ministers%20immediately%20after%20the%20elections%20as%20their%20party%2Falliance%20secured%20a%20majority%20and%20they%20were%20elected%20its%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20all%20three%20occasions%20when%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20won%20as%20a%20sitting%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20he%20secured%20a%20majority%20of%20votes%20in%20his%20constituency.%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20who%20won%20two%20elections%20as%20a%20sitting%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20one%20as%20his%20party's%20Prime%20Ministerial%20candidate%2C%20also%20secured%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20votes%20on%20each%20occasion.%20Indira%20Gandhi%20appears%20in%20the%20list%20four%20times.%20She%20contested%20three%20times%20as%20a%20sitting%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20returning%20to%20power%20twice%20and%20being%20defeated%20once%20in%20her%20own%20seat%2C%20coinciding%20with%20her%20party's%20loss%20in%20the%201977%20election.%20On%20another%20occasion%2C%20she%20won%20the%20election%20and%20helped%20the%20Congress%20return%20to%20power%20after%20three%20years%20in%20the%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAtal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20also%20appears%20four%20times.%20Twice%20he%20was%20a%20sitting%20Prime%20Minister.%20On%20one%20of%20these%20occasions%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20power%20(1999)%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%2C%20his%20party%20was%20voted%20out%20(2004).%20Twice%20he%20became%20Prime%20Minister%20after%20winning%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20from%20his%20constituency%20(1996%2C%201998).%20Notably%2C%20most%20Prime%20Ministers%20listed%20below%20did%20not%20change%20their%20constituencies%2C%20except%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20retained%20Medak%20and%20relinquished%20Raebareli%20in%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20relevant%20to%20note%20that%20except%20in%20three%20cases%20(Narasimha%20Rao%20from%20Berhampur%2C%20Indira%20Gandhi%20from%20Medak%2C%20and%20Morarji%20Desai%20from%20Surat)%2C%20all%20sitting%20Prime%20Ministers%20and%20prospective%20Prime%20Ministers%20in%20the%20table%20won%20from%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20In%20his%20third%20victory%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20saw%20a%20nine-percentage-point%20decline%20in%20his%20vote%20share%20in%20Varanasi.%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20experienced%20an%20eleven-percentage-point%20decline%20in%20vote%20share%20in%20his%20third%20election%20from%20Phulpur.%20The%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituencies%20of%20sitting%20and%20prospective%20Prime%20Ministers%20have%20always%20been%20prestige%20battles.%20There%20has%20been%20only%20one%20defeat%2C%20and%20in%20more%20than%20three-fourths%20of%20the%20cases%2C%20they%20have%20polled%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrime%20Ministers%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20Elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESitting%20Prime%20Ministers%20contesting%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20and%20individuals%20who%20contested%20Lok%20Sabha%20Polls%20and%20became%20Prime%20Minister%C2%A0%3Cem%3E(in%20decreasing%20order%20of%20percentage%20of%20votes%20polled%20by%20candidate)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%20width%3D%5C%22593%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccolgroup%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%2264%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22138%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22136%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22141%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ccol%20width%3D%5C%22114%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fcolgroup%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3EYear%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIndividual%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan